http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Ayyappa-Panicker-lecture-today/article14024415.ece

Jibu Mathew George, Assistant Professor at the Department of Indian and World Literatures attached to the School of Literary Studies of the English and Foreign Languages University in Hyderabad, will deliver this year’s Dr. Ayyappa Panicker memorial lecture, to be organised by the Post-Graduate Department of English at the NSS College at Pandalam on Thursday. Dr. George will talk on ‘The Quotodian intellect: literature, philosophy and everyday life,’ according to the organisers. College Principal D. Gopimohan will preside over the function to be held at the college auditorium. — Special Correspondent